### Simulate Public Access for Payload CMS Collection in Tests

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/ACCESS-CONTROL-ADVANCED.md

This TypeScript snippet illustrates how to test access control for a Payload CMS collection by simulating an unauthenticated (public) user request. It uses `payload.find` with `overrideAccess: false` to enforce access rules and `user: undefined` to mimic a guest, then logs the number of accessible documents.

```typescript
// In test/development
const testAccess = await payload.find({
  collection: 'posts',
  overrideAccess: false, // Enforce access control
  user: undefined // Simulate no user
})

console.log('Public access result:', testAccess.docs.length)
```

