### Query Collections with Local API

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/SKILL.md

Demonstrates local API query patterns including filtering with where clauses, relationship population with depth parameter, pagination, and sorting. Shows difference between depth levels for relationship hydration.

```typescript
// Local API
const posts = await payload.find({
  collection: 'posts',
  where: {
    status: { equals: 'published' },
    'author.name': { contains: 'john' },
  },
  depth: 2,
  limit: 10,
  sort: '-createdAt',
})

// Query with populated relationships
const post = await payload.findByID({
  collection: 'posts',
  id: '123',
  depth: 2, // Populates relationships (default is 2)
})
// Returns: { author: { id: "user123", name: "John" } }

// Without depth, relationships return IDs only
const post = await payload.findByID({
  collection: 'posts',
  id: '123',
  depth: 0,
})
// Returns: { author: "user123" }
```

