### Enable Payload CMS admin auto-login for development

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/authentication/overview.mdx

This configuration snippet illustrates how to enable auto-login for the Payload admin panel, typically for development or testing purposes. It dynamically sets auto-login credentials based on the `NODE_ENV` to ensure it's disabled in production, prefilling user email and password.

```ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

export default buildConfig({
  // ...
  admin: {
    autoLogin:
      process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'
        ? {
            email: 'test@example.com',
            password: 'test',
            prefillOnly: true,
          }
        : false,
  },
})
```

